%N A007565 Number of Go games with n moves.
%C A007565 The sequence is based on a 19 X 19 board which is empty in the initial state. The terms are the partial sums of A048289. - _M. F. Hasler_, Nov 24 2016
%D A007565 Cho Chikun, Go: a Complete Introduction to the Game, Kiseido Publishers, Tokyo, 1997.
%D A007565 N. J. A. Sloane and Simon Plouffe, The Encyclopedia of Integer Sequences, Academic Press, 1995 (includes this sequence).
%D A007565 H. Taylor, personal communication. [Scanned letter will be added. - _N. J. A. Sloane_, Nov 25 2016]
%H A007565 D. Forgues, <a href="https://oeis.org/wiki/Game_of_Go">Game of Go</a>, OEIS wiki, Feb. 2016.
%H A007565 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/Go.html">Go</a>.
%H A007565 Wikipedia, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Go_%28game%29">Go</a>.
%F A007565 a(n) = a(n-1) + A048289(n) for n > 0. - _M. F. Hasler_, Nov 24 2016
